# C# backend context

When editing or reviewing C# in Sig.App.Backend:

- Prefer async/await; avoid .Result/.Wait() on async code.
- Use constructor injection; keep resolvers thin, logic in services.
- Check authorization before operations; validate inputs.
- Avoid N+1 queries; use batch loading or AsNoTracking for read-only.
- For code review requests, apply the code-review-csharp skill (C# code review agent).
